BIB                  5         14
REACTION   (3-LI-7(D,N+A)2-HE-4,,DA/DA/DE,A/A/N+A,MSC)
           Internal energy spectra is given. Relative motion of
           alpha-n rest system is considered (not lab. system nor
           projectile-target centre-of-mass system).
           ANG1 is the angle of detection for the "first" alpha
           particle, ANG2 is the polar angle of the "second"
           emitted alpha particle in the system where the
           alpha-neutron complex is at rest.
ANG-SEC    (ANG1,A)
           (ANG2,A)
EN-SEC     (E-RL,N+A) is the internal energy of the alpha-n system
STATUS     (CURVE,,V.D'Amico+,J,NC/A,22,313,1974) Fig.3
HISTORY    (20251211A) SD: BIB updated. The accuracy of data
           presentation has been revised.
ENDBIB              14
