SUBENT        F0253004   20251211   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  5         15
REACTION   (3-LI-7(D,N+A)2-HE-4,,DA/DA/DE,A/A/N+A,MSC)
           Relative motion of alpha-n rest system is considered
            (not lab. system nor projectile-target centre-of-mass
           system).
ANG-SEC    (ANG1,A)
           ANG1 is an angle of alpha particle detection.
           (ANG2,A)
           ANG2 is a relative angle that can be interpreted as
           the angle of the alpha-particle in the centre of mass
           of the alpha-n system when the motion of this latter is
           described in the system of the centre of mass of the
           three particles.
EN-SEC     (E-RL,N+A) is the internal energy of the alpha-n system
STATUS     (CURVE,,V.D'Amico+,J,NC/A,22,313,1974) Fig.4
HISTORY    (20251211U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB              15
